title: Not ready for prime time
text:
Feels like they rushed to get this to market. Submitted 2 orders, both had the address changed in shipping (?) - so, delivered to another house in our neighborhood which unfortunately doesn’t currently have any occupants.

Never received the items. When trying to select the “Request Refund” option in the app it just displays a message to call customer service (then why have the button???)

It’s back to ordering from Amazon. At least they make returns easier and have a way to contact customer service easily.
